        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa"><!-- Following text is from 1903; draft text not heretofore transcribed electronically, so this text should be carefully corrected against ms -->
                <lg type="stanza">
                <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/><del rend="strikethrough">The</del> Oh the morn looked bright<!--Note: Letters "g" and "t" have lines through them, but are not struckthrough--> o<subst><del>v</del><add rend="overwriting">n</add></subst><del rend="strikethrough">er</del> hill and dale</l>
                    <l>As we left<!--Note: Letter "f" has lines through it, but it is not struckthrough--> the walls of merry<!--Note: Letter "y" has lines through it, but it is not struckthrough--> <unclear>d&#x00E4;yle</unclear></l>
                <l>And towrds the long hill ridges wound</l>
                    <l>That ramparted the plain around<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_contextual.php#DAYLE"/><add rend="linenumber-right-JR">780</add></l>
                <l>That greener growing as we neared</l>
                <l>At length with meadows decked appeared</l>
                <l>Fair as our fields in May; and then</l>
                <pb facs="MSVIII61v"/>
                <l>We entered on a little glen<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">780</add></l>
                    <l>Those miniature <geogName corresp="#ALPS">Alps</geogName> among,<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_contextual.php#MINIATUREALPS"/></l>
                <l>All smiling with a morning sun</l>
                <l>Grassy and woody, and most sweet</l>
                <l>As ever fairy her retreat</l>
                    <l>Formed for her midnight dances,<ref type="gloss_textual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_textual.php#TERMINALCOMMA" /> Through<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">785</add></l>
                <l>Tracing, in mazy winds anew,</l>
                <l>The spots it had passed oer, as fain</l>
                <l>To run its sweet course oer again,&#x2014;</l>
                <l>Flowed a small tributary stream</l>
                    <l>That the <geogName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</geogName> levied all between<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_contextual.php#KINZIGRIVER"/><add rend="linenumber-right-JR">790</add></l>
                    <l>The frontlets of the fair fresh hills<ref type="gloss_textual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_textual.php#FLOWED" /></l>
                <l><subst><add place="above"><space quantity="3" unit="chars"/>Leaped</add><del rend="strikethrough">Sprang</del></subst> merrily the glad young rills,</l>
                <l>Smiling in silver as they sprang,</l>
                <l>And merry were the notes they sang,</l>
                <l>For they were joyful at their birth<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">795</add></l>
                <l>From the cold prisons of the earth</l>
                <l>To the warm sun and open sky,</l>
                <l>And their song was all of liberty</l>
                <l>But the dell narrowed as we went</l>
                <l>Till, twixt the promontories pent<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">800</add></l>
                <l>It upward ran, and the clear stream</l>
                <l>Now forward shot its banks between,</l>
                <l>Fast flashing, till from the obscure</l>
                <l>Emerged we on a lofty moor,</l>
                <l>Open, and shelterless, and bare,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">805</add></l> 
                    <l>And gently undulating far<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_contextual.php#LOFTYMOOR"/></l>
                <l>With here and there a patch of pine</l>
                <l>Breaking the smoothness of its line,</l>
                    <l>Toward the south horizon!<ref type="gloss_textual" target="oh_the_morn_looked_bright_on_hill_and_dale_poem_glosses_textual.php#SOUTHHORIZON" /></l>
                </lg>
